Program: Omnibus
Title: The Real Good King Wenceslas
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376k77
Last Broadcast Date: 06 November 1991
A visit to Wenceslas Square in Prague looking at the story of the King in the Christmas carol. He was a Christian Bohemian ruler in the 10th century, and miracles are associated with his death at the hands of his brother Boleslav.